originalText.text: Jamie is incredible! She's the best acupuncturist I've ever seen. I started seeing her for my shoulder and neck pain, and she's been so attentive and responsive to my needs. We've explored different techniques, areas, and arrangements to ensure that I'm getting the best possible care. Jamie is a true listener, and she's always checking in to make sure I'm comfortable and getting the results I want. I highly recommend her to anyone looking for an amazing acupuncturist. She's truly a gem in the city!

originalText.text: Jamie is a miracle worker. She is warm, welcoming, and gentle. I see her for acupuncture weekly and the frequency of my migraines has drastically dropped. She is also in network with my health insurance (BlueCross) and the copay experience is effortless every time. I highly recommend Jamie’s practice to those with chronic pain, stress, and even those with muscle soreness after the gym! Thanks to her, my overall well-being has improved greatly and I can’t imagine starting my week without a visit to Grounded Acupuncture!

originalText.text: Best acupuncturist in town. Jamie listens to all of your concerns, physical pain or mental hardships, and will make a plan that is suitable for you. I have gone through physical therapies and chiropractors for my back pain, yet in the end it is acupuncture and a healthy balance in life that helped to alleviate the pain. Jamie approaches problems holistically, because everything in the body is connected. Just like the name suggests, every time I walk out of the office, I feel grounded. Highly recommend!

originalText.text: Jamie is incredibly talented and patient. I was nervous about trying acupuncture so she tailored my plan to start very light and gradually intensify as I got more comfortable. We did a six part treatment plan and I signed up for six more!

originalText.text: I’m so happy I found Grounded Acupuncture! Jamie is wonderful - very knowledgeable, thoughtful, and effective. She always remembers what’s going on with me even if it’s been a few weeks between sessions. She’s really helped with issues related to too much stress and screen time and I feel incredible after every session. The space is warm and welcoming with great views and I’ve always felt very safe and comfortable there (this is important as a person who actually hates needles). Highly recommend this practice and loves Jamie’s holistic approach to healing.
